# Preprocessing

### convert char to Date and create duration var

``` r
df$created_as_time <- parse_date_time(df$Created.Date, '%m/%d/%Y %I:%M:%S %p')
df$closed_as_time  <- parse_date_time(df$Closed.Date, '%m/%d/%Y %I:%M:%S %p')

df$duration_time   <- as.numeric(difftime(df$closed_as_time, df$created_as_time)) 
```

#### mean of duration to solve per day of the call

``` r
#created_as_time convert to Date
df$Date <- as.Date(df$created_as_time)


df%>%
  group_by(df$Date)%>%
  mutate(mean_duration = mean(duration_time, na.rm = T))%>%
  distinct(Date, .keep_all = T) -> df_ts
```

### time series incident resolution time

``` r
#time series of duration to solve per date
ts_a <- xts(x = df_ts$mean_duration, order.by = df_ts$Date)
```

### mean of duration until solved issue & number of calls per day

``` r
#if duration<0 => NA
df_ts2 <- df
df_ts2$duration_time[df_ts2$duration_time <0] <- NA


#created_as_time convert to Date
df_ts2$Date <- as.Date(df_ts2$created_as_time)

#compute mean duration & number of calls per day and filter
df_ts2%>%
  group_by(Date)%>%
  mutate(mean_duration = mean(duration_time, na.rm = T))%>%
  mutate(number = n())%>%
  distinct(Date, .keep_all = T) -> df_ts2

#to xts duration daily time series
ts_duration <- xts(x = df_ts2$mean_duration, order.by = df_ts2$Date)

#to xts number of call daily time series
ts_number <- xts(x = df_ts2$number, order.by = df_ts2$Date)
```

# Create a data frame with one Borough

``` r
#remove rows for unspecified Boroughs
c <- c("BRONX", "BROOKLYN", "MANHATTAN", "QUEENS", "STATEN ISLAND")

df %>% filter(Borough %in% c) -> df

#df$Borough[df$Borough == "STATEN ISLAND"] <- "STATEN_ISLAND"

# BRONX first
df_bronx = subset(df, Borough == "BRONX")

df_ = subset(df_bronx, Complaint.Type == "Water System")

#compute mean duration & number of calls per day and filter
df_%>%
  group_by(Date)%>%
  mutate(number = n())%>% 
  distinct(Date, .keep_all = T) -> df_new

df_new$type = "Water System"
df_new$borough = "BRONX"

c = c("Noise", "Air Quality", "Lead", "Water Conservation", "Hazardous Materials", "Water Quality", "Sewer")

for (i in c){
  
  df_ = subset(df_bronx, Complaint.Type == i)
  #compute mean duration & number of calls per day and filter
  df_%>%
    group_by(Date)%>%
    mutate(number = n()) %>% 
    distinct(Date, .keep_all = T) -> df_

  df_$type = i
  df_$borough = "BRONX"
  
  #rbind df
  df_new = rbind(df_new, df_)
  
}
```

### Bind next Boroughs

``` r
list_borough <- c("BROOKLYN", "MANHATTAN", "STATEN ISLAND", "QUEENS")

list_complaint = c("Water System", "Noise", "Air Quality", "Lead", "Water Conservation", "Hazardous Materials", "Water Quality", "Sewer")

#outer-loop
for (borough in list_borough){
  df_ = subset(df, Borough == borough)
  #inner-loop
    for (complaint in list_complaint){
      df_2 = subset(df_, Complaint.Type == complaint)
        #compute mean duration & number of calls per day and filter
        df_2%>%
          group_by(Date)%>%
          mutate(number = n()) %>% 
          distinct(Date, .keep_all = T) -> df_2
        
        df_2$type = complaint
        df_2$borough = borough
        
        #rbind df
        df_new = rbind(df_new, df_2)
      
    }
}
```
